{#-
  Resizable — 2-pane resizable container with drag handle.

  Per OQ-36 (sealed S2.4 opening): event-only persistence — the controller
  dispatches `resizable:change` ; the consumer chooses to persist via
  localStorage / cookie / URL / no persistence. Cohérent kit doctrine
  "no implicit side effects".

  Architecture:
    CSS Grid 2-pane layout with `grid-template-{columns,rows}` deriving
    from `--theme-resizable-size` (set by the controller). The handle
    is a focusable element with role="separator". Keyboard: Arrow keys
    + Home / End. Pointer: drag with pointer capture.

  Composes:
    - `resizable` Stimulus controller (pointer drag + keyboard + dispatch).
    - 0 primitive composition required at this layer ; consumer fills the
      two panes via `{% block start %}` + `{% block end %}` with arbitrary
      content (Card, ScrollArea, raw HTML, etc.).

  grip-vertical icon: CSS-only via mask-image data URI (cohérent Table sort
  + Pagination icons). The Lucide curated 30-icon set doesn't include
  grip-vertical; the CSS-only path avoids amending the icon set mid-ring.

  Parameters:
    htmlId         (string,  optional) — auto-generated.
    orientation    (string,  optional) — horizontal (default) | vertical.
    size           (int,     optional) — initial size of start pane as
                                         percentage of wrap's main-axis (default 50).
    minSize        (int,     optional) — minimum size in percent (default 10).
    maxSize        (int,     optional) — maximum size in percent (default 90).
    step           (int,     optional) — keyboard increment in percent (default 5).
    handleAriaLabel (string, optional) — aria-label on the handle
                                         (default 'Redimensionner').
    className      (string,  optional)

  Blocks:
    start (required) — content of the start pane.
    end   (required) — content of the end pane.

  Usage:

    {% embed '@theme/components/resizable/resizable.html.twig' with {
      orientation: 'horizontal',
      size: 40,
      minSize: 20,
      maxSize: 70,
      handleAriaLabel: 'Redimensionner les panneaux'|trans,
    } %}
      {% block start %}
        <aside>Sidebar content</aside>
      {% endblock %}
      {% block end %}
        <main>Main content area</main>
      {% endblock %}
    {% endembed %}

  Events (dispatched on the wrap):
    resizable:change — detail.{size, orientation}
-#}

{%- set htmlId          = htmlId          | default('theme-resizable-' ~ random()) -%}
{%- set orientation     = orientation     | default('horizontal') -%}
{%- set size            = size            | default(50) -%}
{%- set minSize         = minSize         | default(10) -%}
{%- set maxSize         = maxSize         | default(90) -%}
{%- set step            = step            | default(5) -%}
{%- set handleAriaLabel = handleAriaLabel | default('Redimensionner') -%}
{%- set className       = className       | default('') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['theme-resizable'] -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

<div
  id="{{ htmlId }}"
  class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}"
  data-orientation="{{ orientation }}"
  data-controller="resizable"
  data-resizable-orientation-value="{{ orientation }}"
  data-resizable-size-value="{{ size }}"
  data-resizable-min-size-value="{{ minSize }}"
  data-resizable-max-size-value="{{ maxSize }}"
  data-resizable-step-value="{{ step }}"
  style="--theme-resizable-size: {{ size }}%;"
>
  <div
    id="{{ htmlId }}-start"
    class="theme-resizable__pane theme-resizable__pane--start"
    data-resizable-target="startPane"
  >
    {%- block start -%}{%- endblock -%}
  </div>

  <div
    class="theme-resizable__handle"
    data-resizable-target="handle"
    role="separator"
    aria-orientation="{{ orientation }}"
    aria-controls="{{ htmlId }}-start"
    aria-label="{{ handleAriaLabel }}"
    tabindex="0"
  >
    <span class="theme-resizable__grip" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  </div>

  <div class="theme-resizable__pane theme-resizable__pane--end">
    {%- block end -%}{%- endblock -%}
  </div>
</div>
